49#ifndef TYPES_H_
50#define TYPES_H_
51
52#ifdef HAVE_INTTYPES_H
53#include <inttypes.h>
54#endif
55
56typedef struct pgp_io_t {
57 void *outs; /* output file stream */
58 void *errs; /* file stream to put error messages */
59 void *res; /* file stream to put results */
60} pgp_io_t;
61
62/** pgp_map_t
63 */
64typedef struct {
65 int type;
66 const char *string;
67} pgp_map_t;
68
69/** pgp_errcode_name_map_t */
70typedef pgp_map_t pgp_errcode_name_map_t;
71
72typedef struct pgp_crypt_t pgp_crypt_t;
73
74/** pgp_hash_t */
75typedef struct pgp_hash_t pgp_hash_t;
76
77/** Revocation Reason type */
78typedef uint8_t pgp_ss_rr_code_t;
79
80/** pgp_packet_t */
81typedef struct pgp_packet_t pgp_packet_t;
82
83/** Writer flags */
84typedef enum {
85 PGP_WF_DUMMY
86} pgp_writer_flags_t;
87
88/**
89 * \ingroup Create
90 * Contains the required information about how to write
91 */
92typedef struct pgp_output_t pgp_output_t;
93
94#endif /* TYPES_H_ */
95
